  "text": "Genomic DNA was extracted from tissue samples (heart, liver, lung, cerebrum and cerebellum) by saturated phenol-chloroform extraction method [CITATION_1] ) and stored at -80°C. The concentration of the isolated DNA was determined using a spectrophotometer, diluted to 50 ng μL -1 , and stored at -20°C for subsequent analysis. A total of 1 000 ng individual genomic DNA was finally treated by Sodium bisulfite using EZ DNA Methylation-Gold TM Kit (ZYMO RESEARCH, California, US) strictly following the manufacture's instruction strictly.",
